 CMMG complete upper receiver features 5.56x45 chamber, Free Float Tube handguard, 16" Bull Barrel, made of 4140 Chrome-moly vanadium steel with a 1:9 twist, and an 11 degree recessed target crown. The Flat Top Forged M4 upper receiver is T marked and has M4 feed ramp cuts and a Auto M16 style bolt carrier group. 

W.A.S.P. Treated Barrel (Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding. The nitriding conversion is applied to the barrel inside and out, along with the front sight base on our LE rifles and uppers. Nitriding offers improved wear, abrasion, and corrosion resistance when compared to hard chrome lining or phosphating. 

Unlike chrome lining, where the chrome is built up on the surface, nitrating converts the surface without the risk of dimensional build up. CMMG Pioneered the use of this nitrating process on AR barrels and has been using it for many years. 
Ejection port door, forward assist & shell deflector.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig/Sauer P226 9mm w/5 high capacity magazines
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is my Sig P226 in 9mm. This gun was made in the mid 90s and is an ex-Swiss law-enforcement weapon. It was once issued to an officer of their State Police or Highway Patrol. The slide is the heavier milled stainless steel part instead of the earlier stamped one, and has the Swiss canton regional crest(Vaud) on the left side. Since it was an issued weapon there is some finish wear, but this doesn't affect anything. In fact I think it gives the gun some character. Also, because this gun was made in the 1990s with the updated milled slide, it has none of the problems that some of the newer post-2004 Cohen-era Sig pistols have. This one has the best features from a time when Sig built nothing but the best.

With the pistol comes 5 high capacity mags: 3 factory 15-rounders(including one  post-'94 Ban-era 'zipper-back'), a new Mec/Gar 17-rounder, and a Mec/Gar 20 round mag. If you are left-handed I will include a kydex OWB holster by Shadow Holsters of Minnesota. Ammo in the mag pic not included.

title: For Sale:  9mm Freedom Munitions remanufactured 115gr FMJ - 500 rounds
postcontent:
From the Freedom Munitions website:
FREEDOM MUNITIONS inspects all cartridge cases for defects. The Scharch Range Master machines are fully automated and cases are checked for any debris and pressure tested for any splits or cracks. Primers are removed, flash holes are cleared, and primer pockets are reamed to accept new primers.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS then washes cases in an acid wash specially designed to remove all remaining burnt powder from the flash hole and interior of the case which tumbling doesn't remove. Then cases are tumbled in a dryer for a factory look and finish.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS roll sizes all cases on our own designed machines to meet S.A.A.M.I.specification. This method is the industry standard for commercial sizing, insuring the case wall is sized down to the rim which insures new component performance.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS then loads these processed components on the same fiber optic-controlled Ammo Load machines as our premium new ammo. These are the same machines used by some of the largest manufacturers in the industry. These machines assure S.A.A.M.I. specifications for priming depth, pressure and overall cartridge length.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS "Like-New" manufacturing process with the new projectile, powder and primer assures factory ammo performance that discriminating shooters expect.

I've got 500 rounds (10 boxes of 50) for sale. This has been kept in an ammo can, indoors. This ammo was purchased around January of this year, so it hasn't been sitting long. I'm just trying to consolidate calibers. I've personally shot about 200 rounds of this stuff, and it's great for the range.
